NOTE: /usr/share/dict/words | This file contains one word per line

>>>> grep thon /usr/share/dict/words
match the string "thon" in the list words inside the file
show words that all contain the string thon somewhere inside of them 
passing in grep is case sensitive
needs to be matched exactly

>>>> grep -i thon /usr/share/dict/words
match a string regardless of case

>>>> grep l.rts /usr/share/dict/words
dot in our pattern was substituted by different letter
dot is a wildcard

>>>> grep ^fruit /usr/share/dict/words
match the words in the file that starts with "fruit"
The circumflex(^) indicates the beginning

>>>> grep cat$ /usr/share/dict/words
match the words in the file that ends with "cat"
the dollar($) sign indicates the end of the line